overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser-based testing of the
  sleep questionnaire application. The agent systematically navigated through
  the application, testing the questionnaire flow, report generation, PDF
  download, and admin login. During this process, it confirmed that core
  functionalities like conditional fields, form validation, and API endpoints
  were working as expected. It also identified minor issues such as ESLint
  warnings and an outdated page title. Following the testing, the agent
  proceeded to address these issues and commit a series of significant feature
  enhancements that were already present in the codebase but needed to be
  committed. These enhancements included new fields for pain and chronic
  fatigue, updated mental health questions, a comprehensive sleep health
  analysis in the report, an enhanced PDF report, and a CSV export feature. The
  agent meticulously followed a conventional commit strategy, creating multiple
  atomic commits for each logical change.
